### TITLE ###
Ignore single signal by name
### DESCRIPTION ###
Snapshots run on all platforms, so these cases stick to sigint/sigterm - the
only signals Windows supports (others error there by design). Unix-only
signals like sigpipe are covered by the unix-gated Go test.
### INPUT ###
signal_ignore("sigint")
print("ok")
### STDOUT ###
ok

### TITLE ###
Ignore multiple signals via list
### INPUT ###
signal_ignore(["sigint", "sigterm"])
print("ok")
### STDOUT ###
ok

